1 public swimming pool infrastructure account within the state special revenue fund provided for in 17-2-102 to
2 provide grant funding to nonprofit organizations and local governments that operate public swimming pools and
3 for administrative costs related to administering the grants. The department of commerce shall administer the
4 account.
5
6 (2) Up to 3% of the funds appropriated in [section 8] may be allocated for the department of
7 commerce's administrative costs.
8
9 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Public swimming pool infrastructure grants authorization. (1) The
10 department of commerce is authorized to make up to $5 million in grants to nonprofit organizations and local
11 governments for property acquisition, construction, space acquisition, remodeling, repairs, and the purchase of
12 appliances and equipment related to a public swimming pool. The grants authorized in this section are subject
13 to the conditions set forth in [section 5].
14 (2) The department of commerce shall receive proposals from nonprofit organizations and local
15 governments for public swimming pool infrastructure projects.
16 (3) Funding for projects may be provided only as long as there are sufficient funds available from
17 the amount that was deposited or transferred in the public swimming pool infrastructure account for grants
18 established in [section 2]. Funding for these projects must be made available in the order that the grant
19 recipients satisfy the conditions as described in [section 5].
20
21 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Eligibility -- submission deadline -- priority -- guidelines. (1) A
22 nonprofit organization or local government may apply to the department of commerce for public swimming
23 pools infrastructure grants under [section 3].
24 (2) Nonprofit organizations and local governments shall submit grant applications to the
25 department of commerce in order to be eligible for funding under [section 3].
26 (3) The department of commerce is authorized to adopt guidelines necessary to implement
27 [sections 3 through 6].
28
